              title: "The TVMDC Chain",
              body: "True → Variation → Magnetic → Deviation → Compass\n\nVariation: the angle between True North and Magnetic North (from the chart)\nDeviation: the error caused by the ship's own magnetism (from the deviation card)\nTotal Compass Error (TCE) = Variation + Deviation\nEasterly errors are POSITIVE (+). Westerly errors are NEGATIVE (−).\n\nTo go T → C: subtract easterly errors, add westerly errors.\nTo go C → T: add easterly errors, subtract westerly errors.\n(Or simply: True = Compass + TCE, where TCE = Var + Dev, E positive.)"
