              body: "1. Take the most abeam object FIRST (fastest changing bearing)\n2. Take bearings quickly in succession — not more than 1 minute total\n3. If using a pelorus or bearing compass, have a second person note the time\n4. Transit = no compass error, most accurate PL\n5. Danger bearing = continuous monitoring, no need to plot\n6. Leading line = follow and stay in channel\n7. Radar range is MORE accurate than radar bearing — prefer range circles for fixing\n8. Write down bearings before converting — memory is unreliable under pressure"
