                "The Earth behaves as a large imperfect magnet. The **magnetic poles** do not coincide with the geographic poles — the Magnetic North Pole currently lies in the Canadian Arctic (≈ 86°N, 160°W) and is slowly drifting. The field has a horizontal directing force **H** (which turns the compass needle) and a vertical dipping force **Z** (which pulls the needle down, more so at high latitudes).",
                "## Variation",
