              "**Order of Placing Correctors:**\n1. **Flinders Bar** -- first, as it affects heeling error and is magnetised by other magnets.\n2. **Spheres (Kelvin balls)** -- before permanent magnets, as they affect and are affected by them.\n3. **Heeling Error Magnets** -- before horizontal correctors, as they induce Coefficient B in the Flinders bar.\n4. **Fore-and-Aft Magnets** (Coefficient B correction) -- usually done before athwartships because B is usually larger.\n5. **Athwartships Magnets** (Coefficient C correction).\n\nAll soft iron correctors must be in position before final adjustment of permanent corrector magnets.",
              "**Pre-Swing Checks (ship laid up):**\n1. Vessel must be upright; all derricks, cranes, boats in seagoing position.\n2. Test compass for friction (deflect with magnet, check it returns).\n3. Check lubber line for fore-and-aft accuracy.\n4. Check azimuth mirror accuracy.\n5. All movable gear near compass in seagoing position. No loose metal nearby.\n6. No ship within 3 cables.\n7. Test soft iron correctors for retained magnetism by rotating spheres and end-for-ending Flinders bar top piece. Remove residual magnetism by annealing (heat to 700C, cool slowly).",
