                "The gyro compass is a non-magnetic compass that seeks and maintains **True North** by exploiting two fundamental properties of a spinning gyroscope interacting with the Earth's rotation. Modern ships use the gyro compass as the primary heading reference for steering, radar, ARPA, and ECDIS.",
                "## Gyroscopic Property 1 — Rigidity in Space",
