                "Spring tides produce the **highest high waters** and **lowest low waters** — maximum tidal range. They occur approximately **2 days after** the new/full moon (due to the 'age of the tide' — inertia of the ocean).",
                "## Neap Tides — Minimum Range",
                "When the Moon is at **first or last quarter**, the Moon and Sun are at approximately 90° to each other as seen from the Earth (**quadrature**). Their tidal forces partially cancel, producing **neap tides**:",
