              title: "No-Go Areas, Clearing Lines and Wheel-Over Positions",
              body: "A No-Go Area is any area the vessel must not enter — shallow water below minimum UKC, submerged wrecks, TSS prohibited zones, or military exercise areas. On the chart it is marked as a shaded zone bounded by the UKC safety contour. The safety contour is set in ECDIS to equal charted depth + tidal height that is greater than or equal to ship's draught + minimum UKC. A Clearing Bearing is a bearing of a charted object beyond which the vessel is clear of a danger — the vessel keeps the object bearing more than (or less than) the stated value. A Wheel-Over Position (WOP) is calculated by applying a turning circle to the intended new track: the helm is put over at the WOP so that the vessel steadies on the new course at the planned track. Parallel index lines set on the radar at the correct distance from a conspicuous radar target allow the OOW to verify in real time that the vessel is maintaining the planned track."
