                "The International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea (SOLAS) is the most important international treaty governing maritime safety. It contains 14 chapters (including sub-chapters), each addressing a specific area of ship safety. Every 2nd Mate candidate must know the chapter numbers and their subject matter.",
                "Chapter I — General Provisions: Covers survey and certification requirements. Defines the scope and application of the convention, survey types (initial, renewal, annual, intermediate, additional), and the certificates issued.",
                "Chapter II-1 — Construction — Subdivision and Stability, Machinery and Electrical Installations: Covers structural requirements, watertight subdivision, stability in damaged condition, bilge pumping, steering gear, and electrical installations.",
