                "Chapter III — Life-Saving Appliances and Arrangements: Covers requirements for lifeboats, life rafts, life jackets, lifebuoys, immersion suits, pyrotechnics, EPIRB, SART, line-throwing apparatus, and muster lists.",
                "Chapter IV — Radio Communications: Covers GMDSS (Global Maritime Distress and Safety System) requirements, sea areas A1-A4, equipment carriage requirements, and distress alerting procedures.",
                "Chapter V — Safety of Navigation: Covers passage planning (Reg. 34), bridge equipment requirements, danger messages, meteorological services, routing of ships, VTS, and mandatory ship reporting systems.",
