                "Formula: The sound pulse travels to the seabed and back (distance = 2S). Speed of sound through sea water is taken as 1500 m/s. Therefore: 2S = V x T, so S = (V x T) / 2, where S = depth, V = speed of sound (1500 m/s), T = time for round trip in seconds.",
                "## How to Confirm Echo Sounder is Working",
