                "## GHA, SHA, and the Nautical Almanac",
                "For the **Sun, Moon, and planets**, the Nautical Almanac tabulates GHA and Declination for every hour of every day of the year. You interpolate for the exact minutes and seconds using the 'increments and corrections' pages.",
                "For **stars**, the almanac uses a more compact system. It tabulates the GHA of the **First Point of Aries (γ)** — a reference point on the celestial equator. Each star's position is given as its **SHA (Sidereal Hour Angle)** — the westward angle from Aries to the star. To find a star's GHA: **GHA★ = GHA Aries + SHA★**.",
                "## The Sides and Angles of the PZX Triangle",
