                body: "**Stage 1 — Wave formation:** A wave develops on the polar front. Low pressure forms at the apex. Warm and cold fronts develop.\n\n**Stage 2 — Deepening:** Low deepens (pressure falls), fronts extend. Isobars become more circular. System intensifies.\n\n**Stage 3 — Mature:** Well-developed low. Fronts well separated. Warm sector at sea level between fronts.\n\n**Stage 4 — Occlusion:** Cold front catches warm front. Warm sector lifted off surface. Occlusion forms. System begins to fill.\n\n**Stage 5 — Filling:** Low fills (pressure rises). Fronts weaken. System dissipates.\n\n**Track:** Depressions generally track NE in NH (following upper-level flow). In SH, they track SE. Depth and track are steered by upper-level jet stream."
