              body: "Hygroscopic cargo (grain, coffee, jute): prolonged high humidity causes mould, heating, and cargo quality loss — never ventilate when outside air is more humid than the hold.\n\nCoal holds: coal oxidation produces CO (carbon monoxide — toxic) and CH₄ (methane — explosive). Test atmosphere before entry every time. Do not ventilate into a heating hold — fresh oxygen accelerates oxidation.\n\nGrain holds: biological respiration depletes O₂ and produces CO₂. An oxygen-deficient atmosphere can exist even when the hold appears normal. Always test O₂ level before entry."
