                "The IMSBC Code requires that cargoes with a low angle of repose be thoroughly trimmed level in each hold. An untrimmed cargo with a peaked surface will shift when the ship rolls, creating a dangerous list. The master should ensure that trimming is carried out properly and should verify the state of the cargo surface before closing hatches."
