            id: "t-law-4-1",
            name: "MARPOL — All Annexes",
            content: `**MARPOL 73/78 (International Convention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships)**

MARPOL is the main international convention covering prevention of pollution of the marine environment by ships. It combines two treaties (1973 Convention and 1978 Protocol) and has 6 Annexes.

**Annex I — Oil (Mandatory)**
- Prevents pollution by oil in bilge water and tank washings
- **ORB Part I** (engine room): record all oil operations — bilge pumping, oil transfer, disposal of oily residues
- **ORB Part II** (cargo operations): for tankers — loading, discharge, ballast, tank washing
- **Discharge criteria outside special areas**:
  - Ship must be proceeding on course (underway)
  - ≥12 nm from nearest land
  - Oil content of effluent <15 ppm
  - Ship must have an operational OWS (Oily Water Separator) and OCM (Oil Content Monitor)
- **Special Areas** (NO discharge): Mediterranean, Baltic, Black Sea, Red Sea, "Gulfs Area", North Sea, Antarctic, NW European waters
- **SOPEP** (Shipboard Oil Pollution Emergency Plan): required on all ships ≥400 GT

**Annex II — Noxious Liquid Substances (NLS) in Bulk (Mandatory)**
- Applies to chemical tankers carrying NLS in bulk
- Substances categorised: X (major hazard), Y (hazard), Z (minor hazard), OS (other substances)
- Cargo Record Book (CRB) required

**Annex III — Harmful Substances in Packaged Form (Mandatory)**
- IMDG Code is the implementation instrument
- Packaging, marking, labelling, documentation, stowage, segregation requirements

**Annex IV — Sewage (Mandatory)**
- Ships ≥400 GT or certified for >15 persons
- Discharge of untreated sewage prohibited within 12 nm from nearest land
- Exception: ship proceeding at ≥4 knots, comminuted/disinfected sewage beyond 3 nm
- Ships must have approved sewage treatment plant OR comminuting/disinfecting system OR holding tank

**Annex V — Garbage (Mandatory)**
- **Complete ban on discharge of plastics** anywhere at sea
- Food waste: ≥3 nm (comminuted ≥12 nm) outside special areas; ≥12 nm inside special areas
- All other garbage (paper, rags, glass, metal, cargo residues): PROHIBITED everywhere
- **Garbage Management Plan** required for ships ≥100 GT
- **Garbage Record Book** required for ships ≥400 GT / passenger ships

**Annex VI — Air Pollution (Mandatory)**
- **Sulphur content of fuel oil (SOx)**:
  - Global cap: **0.50% m/m** (since 1 January 2020 — "IMO 2020")
  - ECAs (SECA — Baltic, North Sea, North America, US Caribbean): **0.10% m/m**
  - Compliance: low-sulphur fuel (LSFO/MGO) OR exhaust gas cleaning system (scrubber)
- **NOx**: Tier I, II, III emission standards for marine diesel engines; Tier III in NOx ECAs (~80% reduction)
- **SEEMP** (Ships Energy Efficiency Management Plan): required for all ships ≥400 GT
- **EEDI**: applies to new ships — minimum efficiency standard
- **CII** (Carbon Intensity Indicator): operational rating A–E for ships ≥5000 GT (from 2023)

**Key Documents Summary**

| Document | Applies to |
|---|---|
| ORB Part I | All ships ≥400 GT |
| ORB Part II | Oil tankers ≥150 GT |
| Garbage Record Book | Ships ≥400 GT / passenger ships |
| SOPEP | Ships ≥400 GT |
| IOPP Certificate | Ships ≥400 GT |
| SEEMP | Ships ≥400 GT |`,
