                body: "The Life-Saving Appliances (LSA) Code (IMO Resolution MSC.48(66)) provides international design, testing, and performance standards for all life-saving appliances required by SOLAS Chapter III. SOLAS Chapter III covers requirements for lifeboats, rescue boats, liferafts, lifebuoys, lifejackets, immersion suits, EPIRBs, SARTs, and pyrotechnics. The LSA Code was made mandatory under SOLAS III/34 and applies to ships on international voyages. Passenger ships and cargo ships have different requirements — cargo ships require lifeboats on each side capable of holding all persons on board, plus liferafts. All survival craft must be maintained in a ready-for-use condition at all times."
